<br>
Monk FDs after zonin' in to watch entrance.<br>
<br>
Buff up a pally, SoW him, then send 'im in when no wanderers are near. Then all he's gotta do is run around agroin' every mob he sees and drag 'em all to some corner of the zone and run around in circles. Everyone else quickly zones in, gets to safe spot, waits for pally to die... quick rez and you're on your way!<br>
<br>
<br>
There may be other tactics involvin' lotsa deaths and slow breakins, but I dunno about 'em. <p><p align="center"><a href="http://pub75.ezboard.com/btheshoemakers"><img src="http://www.pwshift.com/tr/images/fimble_transparent.gif" alt="Fimble Fetishists!" align="center" border="0"></a><BR>email: <a href="mailto:fimble@sevendragons.net">fimble@sevendragons.net</a><BR>AIM: FimbleMT</p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#102960><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub169.ezboard.com/bmtboards.showUserPublicProfile?gid=ishinrublendermonk>Ishinru BlenderMonk</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Lonely in Kera Ridge</span><br>  Posts: 178<br> <font color=#628CBC>(11/14/02 12:22:15 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub169.ezboard.com/fmtboardsfrm35.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=54.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: PoF guides?? </span><hr size=1> I've done Fimble's version in Hate (send monk in first doing the chicken run - aggro all mobs on the south wall and the patrol routes)... never tried it in Fear <br>
<br>
Group like you do any other raid.  For expedency (sic), bring more than one capable puller and have them in the same group so they can communicate where corpses are... DTs will happen unexpectedly.<br>
<br>
Break in always went fine when we:<br>
FD1 runs in and FD at portal.<br>
FD2 runs in and FDs half-way or allt he way to safe-spot on zone wall.  Preferable location would be at the wall so that FD2 has an unobstructed view of any wanderers around the hill.<br>
<br>
When safe spot is clear of wanderers - send in the MA and SA groups. (presuming that they are in different group and each group has its own mezzer.)<br>
<br>
Once the groups reach the safe spot, if only 1 or 2 adds, kill them then invite everyone else to join you.  Otherwise, mez adds and gain control.  Once control is established, allow others to zone in.<br>
<br>
If team wipes, (this never happened to me, so not sure) I'd send in rezzers one at a time until one makes it to safe spot to start the rezzing.  Once the previously wiped break team is back to health, allow others to zone in.  At this point you have 2 full teams, a couple extra rezzers, and the new arrival teams to help gain control.<br>
<br>
Just keep the baddies mezzed and *gain control*.  Meaning - control your raid party.  If they are not attacking the same thing as the MA and/or SA, then mezzes get broke, enchanters will die, mobs won't get re-mezzed, clerics die, everyone dies.<br>
